This position supports student services by helping implement student policies, coordinating required extra-curricular activities for graduation, assisting with bus services, and keeping student information on the ASA website up to date.

- Manage student bus service;
- Handle policy affairs for students (exemption of military service, tuition fee delay, tuition fee reduction, etc.); update students on new policies and regulations via different channels (email, posting on the VGU website, etc.);
- Advise students on university policies and procedures, ensuring awareness and compliance;
- Conduct training/info sessions/meetings/events to educate students and staff on relevant policies and procedures regarding student policies;
- Organize extra-curricular student activities required as conditions for granting degrees;
- Coordinate the process of issuing student ID cards to students;
- Coordinate, request and distribute VGU T-shirts to students, faculty, staff, alumni, and other members appropriately;
- Issue testimony certificates proving students' enrollment status (testimony, reference letter, enrolment certificate, late graduation, etc.);
- Stay current with relevant laws, regulations, and best practices in student affairs for student policy and support;
- Provide information on VGU services and procedures;
